article.headline: Schuknecht has 26 points to lead Sooners to win
article.linkText: Oklahoma defeats instate rival for eighth straight time
article.story:
NORMAN, Okla. (AP) -- Theresa Schuknecht scored a season-high 28
points and grabbed seven rebounds, leading (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP) Oklahoma to an 87-71 victory over Oklahoma State on Sunday.

	   The Sooners (14-8, 5-4 Big 12) ended their first three-game
losing streak since the 1998-99 season. Oklahoma State (5-15, 1-8)
lost its sixth in a row and has now lost eight straight to its
instate rival.

	   Chelsi Welch scored 17 points, and Maria Villarroel and Dionnah
Jackson had 11 each. The Sooners shot 53 percent and took better
care of the ball than in recent games, committing 14 turnovers.

	   Trisha Skibbe scored 23 to lead the Cowgirls. Shelby Hutchins
had 12 and Chantoya Hawkins 11.
